title.narrative: 2.4 RSRCH-BASED SOCIAL & B'HVRAL CHG COMM

description.narrative: Output 2.4 Government ministries and research institutions have strengthened institutional capacities for undertaking research- based social and behavioural change communication, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Outcome 2: By 2020, strengthened commitment and environment promoting child-centred social inclusion, disparity reduction and resilience.

title.narrative: Output 2.4 Government ministries and research institutions have strengthened institutional capacities for undertaking research-based social and behavioural change communication

description.narrative: UNICEF has strengthened institutional capacity in Social and Behaviour Change Communication (SBCC) through the two additional C4D Centres at renowned national universities:;Universiti;Putra Malaysia (UPM) and the National University of Malaysia (UKM), bringing the total to three UNICEF-supported C4D centres in the country.;UNICEF has mainstreamed the SBCC approaches within Health Education Division (HED) and Institute for Health Behavioural Research (IHBR) at the Ministry of Health (MoH) in Risk Communication and Community Engagement (RCCE) response to COVID-19, health behavioural research, and SBCC training curriculum development for health workers.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
